# .trivyignore — accepted / false-positive Trivy findings
#
# Format:  <CVE-ID>  [optional comment]
# Trivy picks this file up automatically when run from the repo root.
#
# To identify findings: open the PR → GitHub Security tab → Code scanning alerts
# Add the CVE-ID here with a justification, then re-run the scan.
#
# Example:
#   CVE-2024-XXXXX  # requests < 2.32: not exploitable via this app's usage pattern

